Capitalism consists mostly of private ownership of the means of
production and lightly regulated or unregulated markets for exchanging
the items (and services) produced. Capitalism is totally at odds with
the collective ownership of land and the means of production. Capitalism
is totally at odds with the Command Economy. Goods and services are
produced when and where there are the means of production and the
opportunity to profit.

The only issues with capitalism are the production of public goods,
where a good or service is necessary but making a profit is difficult or
impossible. Example: Light houses. How do you charge the captain of a
ship at sea for using the light from your lighthous. Answer: you can't.
The other issue is regulating markets to prevent fraud and misleading
practices. How stringent shall that regulation be? This is both an
economic and a political issue.

