Ron Allen answers:
Although a society may be capitalist, such a
society is not self-governed; but rather, a
capitalist society is governed by capital, or by a
political state that is influenced by capital.

Socialists believe that a society which is under
the authority of capital, or under the dominion of
the state, is a poor and faulty society, weak and
lame, frail and fragile, powerless and spiritless,
disabled and deformed, etc.  Also, socialists
believe that a class-divided society is not a
genuine, natural society.

<QUOTE PREVIOUSPOST="
