&gt; implementation of collectivist principles. . . .

Ron Allen answers:
Socialism is often specified by marxists as the
transitional stage between capitalism and
communism; but, even marxists often use the two
words -- socialism and communism -- as names for
the very same social arrangement, as synonyms for
the very same identical organization of society.

