Thank you.

However, not everyone can agree with your
assertion that capitalism is not a social system,
or that capitalism is not a government.  If the
capitalist system is a means and method of
structuring money and banking, of managing and
directing capital and investment, then surely
capitalism is a social system governed by a
national state.  Really-existing capitalism is
what socialists condemn; just as really-existing
socialism is what capitalists condemn.

Capitalist models of libertarian anarchism see
freedom as both anti-democratic and anti-
egalitarian, and this agrees with the existing
status quo.  Libertarian and anarchist capitalists
dislike democracy and politics.  These capitalists
believe that producers ought to be excluded from
political power, and this is seen as a good thing,
an ideal arrangement.

